# ADR-0057 — ask the Robometer reward monitor (kind: "reward") how the CURRENT
# task is progressing / succeeding, on demand, over a rolling window.
#
# Called by the reasoner's read-only `query_task_progress` tool dispatch. The
# reward monitor node continuously buffers the co-active VLA's camera frames and
# scores the requested window with the NF4 Robometer model, returning per-frame
# normalized progress + success aggregated to a windowed assessment. Read-only:
# the signal is ADVISORY (it feeds the replanning ladder), never actuation.
#
# Request:
#   window_s — how many seconds of recent frames to assess. Clamped to the
#              monitor's configured frame_window_s.
#   task     — the natural-language task instruction the VLA is executing; sent
#              to the reward model alongside the frames. Empty = reuse the
#              instruction the monitor was last given.
#
# Response:
#   ok             — true iff a frame window was available and the sidecar scored
#                    it. False on stale/no-frame or sidecar error.
#   progress_now   — normalized progress in [0,1] at the latest frame.
#   success_now    — success probability in [0,1] at the latest frame.
#   progress_trend — least-squares slope of progress over the window (per frame).
#   success_trend  — least-squares slope of success over the window (per frame).
#   stalled        — true iff |progress_trend| is ~0 (no progress over the window).
#   succeeded      — true iff success_now >= the manifest success_threshold.
#   frames_seen    — number of frames scored in the window.
#   stale          — true iff no fresh frame arrived within the staleness deadline.

float64 window_s
string task
---
bool ok
float64 progress_now
float64 success_now
float64 progress_trend
float64 success_trend
bool stalled
bool succeeded
int32 frames_seen
bool stale
